data.meta_description: Coorgi Language - Free download as Word Doc (.doc), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The Dasara celebrations this time were held in a very simple way due to drought conditions affecting half of Karnataka state. Around 75% of the funds meant for Dasara were used for drought relief. There was only a Jambu savari procession with cultural programs and torch light parade cancelled. Chief Minister S.M. Krishna inaugurated the procession. Crowds were much lesser than the previous year. There were no special guests at people's homes as many had exams. The exhibition was also very dull with unchanged entry fees.
